$$
\begin{aligned}
& p_{\pi^{0}}=p_{\mathrm{n}} \\
& E_{\mathrm{n}}=m_{\pi^{-}}+m_{\mathrm{p}}-E_{\pi^{0}}
\end{aligned}
$$

Using $E^{2} - p^{2} = m^{2}$, and the invariant mass formula $\left(m_{\pi^{-}} + m_{\mathrm{p}}\right)^{2} = \left(E_{\mathrm{n}} + E_{\pi^{0}}\right)^{2} - \left(p_{\mathrm{n}} - p_{\pi^{0}}\right)^{2}$, from the above two equations we get:

$$
\begin{aligned}
E_{\pi^{0}} & =\frac{\left(m_{\pi^{-}}+m_{\mathrm{p}}\right)^{2}+m_{\pi^{0}}^{2}-m_{\mathrm{n}}^{2}}{2(m_{\pi^{-}}+m_{\mathrm{p}})}=137.62 \, \mathrm{MeV} \\
\gamma & =\frac{E_{\pi^{0}}}{m_{\pi^{0}}}=1.019 \\
\beta & =\sqrt{1 - \frac{1}{\gamma^2}}=0.194 \\
v & =\beta c=0.194 \times 3 \times 10^{8} = 5.8 \times 10^{7} \, \mathrm{m/s}
\end{aligned}
$$

